        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=62262&amp;TOPIC_ID=7463&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Gear+Suggestions&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Ears- leave em alone for now unless you swap for electrum. not a huge difference either way. money best spent elsewhere.</P><P>Face- crystal spider eyes. Sell the enshrouded veil for it's sadly inflated price. That will give you more cash for other upgrades (depending on your server economy..on my enshrouded goes for more)</P><P>neck- /shrug no clue. Go for the black saphire velium neck? probably wouldn't touch it until you can raid for better or it's the worst slot you have.</P><P>Head- nice for the int. leave it until you find a significant upgrade later.</P><P>fingers- i got my ring of the frost spider for 100pp. seen shandel bandit rings for 900pp. good enough as is though.</P><P>wrists-good enough as is. working on getting myself a supple scale armband, but that's going to be near impossible for you at your level. </P><P>arms- good enough</P><P>hands- grey flesh > coldain skin. I love my gloves. get a pair and you will notice the difference. At least I did.</P><P>shoudlers- good enough, swap to elder wolf hide if you can spare the change. not a primary concern IMO. </P><P>chest- same as mine, anything better will cost an arm and a leg or is too high for you to quest (you could MQ, but it costs substantial pp)</P><P>back- same as mine again. I'll probably keep mine until I can either get a heiro camp group or have enough change to spare to buy one.</P><P>belt- same as mine...good enough as is..best you can get for the money that i've seen. again, servers may vary.</P><P>leggs- i'm looking into grey flesh myself. Costly though. this is a prime upgrade spot, but anything you swap to will reduce your funds drastically)</P><P>feet- this and your hands are probably the best two to upgrade first. netted kelp lined shoes are nice. </P><P>primary slot- if you can afford it get a sorcerous bowl or get a good group and go camp it. possible at your level. a pain, but possible</P><P>secondary slot- if you were a dark elf(which since you're a betoxx follower i guess not :) ) I'd say do the newbie book quest there. it's actually a very nice no drop book. it's the only thing different then what my profile shows because it's not listed. Otherwise just keep the stein for now.</P><P>range- mana pres 2 will help you more right now then any other upgrade you can afford for that slot. stick with it for now</P><P>hope that was what you was looking for, but it's just what I would do. If you didn;'t want opinions then you wouldn't have posted though. [:p}</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_blank">Charbonez Soulmark</a><BR>Duzzil Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
