         <strong>Hi all!</strong></P><P>Thanks for all the great advice! (Especially to Charbonez who wrote a very detailed run down!)</P><P>I went up to the bazaar last night and did a bit of upgrading.  Here is what I bought and why:</P><P>Electrum Black Sapphire Earrings (to replace Golden Blach Sapphire Earrings): This give me 20hp at the loss of 20mana.  Not a bad trade-off as a Necro!  I found a great jeweler who simply traded my Golden's for Electrum's for 100pp.  </P><P>Velium Black Sapphire Necklace (to replace Velium Sapphire Necklace):  It was tought to part with 8int/8str, but in the end 65hp/65mana is simply more important to me pre-55.  Cost: 650pp.</P><P>Spider Fur-Lined Boots (to replace Shadowbound Boots):  So I gave up 15hp/15mana for 45hp/5cha.  Here I just wanted 30 more hp.  I suppose I could save for Coldain Skin Boots but really 45hp is more important to me now then the INT and MANA on the CSB.  I plan on upgrading my gloves or pants next to Grey Flesh anyways, so that will make up for my INT loss.</P><P>I got an AMAZING deal last night on a Rod of Oblation.  Only 80pp!  I think he mismarked it, 800pp is closer to its 1000-1500pp value.  I actually didn't know what this was until I did a Primary/Mana search.  It is a 6/27 60mana 1hb 10svf 10svc weapon.  I have a WIZ alt so I did a quick MANA seach and found it!  I replaced my Harvester with it and my mana bar jumped down 2percent!  Holy Crap, thats a TON of mana at my level!  </P><P>So the Rod made up for all my INT mana loss!</P><P><strong>Results of my "tweaking":</strong></P><P>INT went down 13 points.</P><P>Mana went down 7 points.</P><P>HP went UP 115 points. (Up to 1016 at level 37, not bad!) This is 8 free ticks of CoB and to ME that makes it all worth it because I wait about 20 ticks between battles and CoB was getting me too low on health, so I would have to use AoD. Now I can now solo better/faster/safer/and more effective.</P><P>STR went down 13 (Harvester gave me 5 but weighed 8, Sapphire Velium gave me 8) but I bought an EE bag (70percent WR) for 350pp to make up for it :)</P><P><strong>Question: Why Grey Flesh over CSG?  I just don't get why you would want:</strong></P><P>GFG: dex10 int6 wis6 hp20 mana25 svc10 <BR>OVER <BR>CSG: sta9 (the important part!) int6 wis6 hp20 mana20?</P><P>At level 37 the GFG give 5 more mana, but the CSG give 13 more HP! (The 9 STA converts to 13hp at 37, even MORE at highter levels!)  Is it for the DEX?</P><P>I just can't see the reasoning for wanting a high DEX, HP are KING as a necro aren't they?</P><P>I know a lot of you feel that I should just be on the XP hunt, and I completely agree, last night I did 40percent of a level before I went up to bazaar.  I came down from bazaar and XP'd some more and it was MUCH faster since I could CoB more.  So it WAS worth my time to upgrade.  And it will be VERY worth my time to get these upgrades: Sorcerous Bowl, Elder Wolf Hide, CSG, Grey Flesh Trousers, BECAUSE 148hp makes a HUGE difference when soloing with CoB up.  And when I hit 49 and get Lich I will be thanking myself for upgrading to HP gear (not bad INT either!)</P><P>I did change my Short Term Goals to be a bit more realistic. I probably won't be able to afford a Froggy Robe (or a Djarns/Shadel ring or Bone Studded Bracelet) since I'm actually not twinking.  Levels 29-34 was in OOT (see guide) killing sisters for her 12plat sword.  Recently I've been killing Rangers/Druids in EC/WC for the money.  I'm making about 200pp per hour there and there are 3 duo spawns, more than enough for people to share.  Not to mention 22percent of a level an hour!</P><P>Again thanks to everyone for all their suggestions!</P><P></P><P><strong>Deedrok - Level 37<BR>  Necromancer of E'ci<BR>  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234678" target="_blank">My Gear</a></strong><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
