         Yep...I say grey flesh is > than coldain skin gloves for the effect. At your level you will get more use out of the efficiency2 then the extra small gain of hp (18 give or take) you recieved from the coldain.</P><P>Heck, I got my grey flesh gloves at 46 and I never regret buying them. They still save me mana on some of my every day use spells. (51, bub from 52) </P><P>But to each their own. The important thing is just being happy and enjoying your character. <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle> skill > levels > gear The cash will come with the levels. </P><P>As Xzzy said, the person behind the keyboard will make the biggest difference in how good a necromancer is. Gear just gives you more options and flexibility to play with. </P><P>Happy to help in any way I can, just as you'll find most of the other necros here are.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_blank">Charbonez Soulmark</a><BR>Duzzil Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
