         Remember, different people experience different things through their eq career. I'm 51 and still wearing a batfang headband. Why?</P><P>I quit EQ for about 6-7 months to play daoc. I had no thoughts of comming back and stripped my main and all alts down to nothing. I gave this stuff away to friends and my old guild and canceled my account. Daoc was too easy and got boring quick. I decided to come back and reactivated my account. I've been slowly rebuilding my gear since. </P><P>I've had offers from friends to rebuild my equipment, but it's in my nature to aquire my things myself (or enlist the minimum help necisary in aquiring things I can not get myself). I also worry more about traveling Norath with my online friends, gaining my levels, and perfecting my arts then I do about my gear. /shrug It's just not my thing. Don't get me wrong, I'd love to have the uber gear, but I've done just fine without it.</P><P>Some people just don't want to spend the time camping those money camps either. Those like me would rather go exploreing while gaining our levels and therefore tend to aquire less since we take the road less traveled (it's less traveled because the loot vs risk sucks...heh) </P><P>Not flaming or anything, just showing the other side of the coin. <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_blank">Charbonez Soulmark</a><BR>Duzzil Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
