        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I completely agree with Charbonez.  Skills as a necro is MOST important.  </P><P>Learning to Root Rot at 34 was one of the funnest times for me.  Also learning to ST split effectively was a challenge.  It was fun when ST resisted to learn how to get out of a situation of 2 MOB's running at you wantint to kill ya!  Sure its easy for a Chanter to control the situation, but for a necro it a bit more challenging!</P><P>If you didn't know how to split the Duo spawn or Rangers/Druids in WC then how can you fight em?</P><P>Knowing how to do the skills the make necros great is the MOST important thing to learn.  But once you learn all that (which may take ya 60 levels!) having some decent gear becomes important to sustain a killing spree.  And for me, taking the time to upgrade HP is important so that I can keep CoB on longer, so I can regain mana faster, so I can kill faster.</P><P>People tell me: Just level.  Well I am leveling!  And I level faster with good gear!  So it is worth my time to upgrade, especially since I AM making the money now.  So for me there is no reason NOT to upgrade!  Plus it is SO easy and fast to buy gear now with the bazaar features!</P><P><BR>Deed out.</P><P><BR><strong>Deedrok - Level 37<BR>  Necromancer of E'ci<BR>  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234678" target="_blank">My Gear</a></strong><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
